query: Give the names of the schools with the percent eligible for free meals in K-12 is more than 0.1 and test takers whose test score is greater than or equal to 1500?
good_sql: SELECT T2.`School Name` FROM satscores AS T1 INNER JOIN frpm AS T2 ON T1.cds = T2.CDSCode WHERE CAST(T2.`Free Meal Count (K-12)` AS REAL) / T2.`Enrollment (K-12)` > 0.1 AND T1.NumGE1500 > 0

query: State the names and full communication address of high schools in Monterey which has more than 800 free or reduced price meals for ages 15-17?
good_sql: SELECT T1.`School Name`, T2.Zip, T2.Street, T2.City, T2.State FROM frpm AS T1 INNER JOIN schools AS T2 ON T1.CDSCode = T2.CDSCode WHERE T2.County = 'Monterey' AND T1.`Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)` > 800 AND T1.`School Type` = 'High Schools (Public)'

notes.instructions: Elementary School District refers to DOC = 52; Monthly average number of schools that opened in 2018 = count(schools that opened in 1980) / 12

query: What is the ratio of merged Unified School District schools in Orange County to merged Elementary School District schools?
good_sql: SELECT CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN DOC = 54 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS REAL) / SUM(CASE WHEN DOC = 52 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) FROM schools WHERE StatusType = 'Merged' AND County = 'Orange'

notes.instructions: Elementary School District refers to DOC = 52; Unified School District refers to DOC = 54.

query: Which different county has the most number of closed schools? Please provide the name of each school as well as the closure date.
